
Service Location Protocol {{{1
	frequently used for locating printers
	supported by Mac until OSX 10.1
	UDP port 427
	used by HP Network Device Rediscovery Service hpqnrs08.exe

Zeroconf {{{1 
	less strict
	
	Derivations
		Bonjour
			closed-source, c 2002
			UDP port 5353
			'small number' of VPN clients will block
			Win app: mDNSResponder.exe
		Avahi
			open source fork of Bonjour	

services {{{2
http://www.dns-sd.org/ServiceTypes.html

Printing 
	Spooler (more commonly known as "LPR printing" or "LPD printing")
	Protocol http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc1179.txt
	Bonjour Printing http://developer.apple.com/networking/bonjour/BonjourPrinting.pdf

Universal Plug and Play (UPnP) {{{1 
	uses SOAP for message passing
	maybe supported by Intel due to heavier processing requirements

